  "body": "# Problem\nIt is often difficult for translation contributors to see the context in which copy appears, as a result translations don't always fit context or UI. Allowing translation contributors to easily switch language in the app helps them review and adapt copy in context\n\n\n## User story\nAs a translation contributor I want to view the app in my native language, without having to change the language settings of my phone, because it makes it easier for me to review copy\n\n![Screenshot_20210214-220736_Status](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35233054/107972075-984dd980-6fb3-11eb-8894-3d77a76ed1ad.jpg)\n\n\n## Implementation\n\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- User can set preferred language in Settings\n- Default language is set to device language\n- Preferred language setting persist when closing and reopening the app\n\n\n## Notes\nChanging language setting helps find and correct translations where needed. More convenient would be to view screenshots for all new copy in Lokalise when translating. Unfortunately, this requires a lot of manual work. Any way to automate could also be a good solution\n\n\ncc @jinhojang6",
